			<div class="content" id="post-content-1231610">
									

<p>Forgive me, but I feel I'm not expressing myself clearly.</p>
<p>The following facts are assumed:</p>
<ul>
<li>Rocks attack vessels approaching the island.</li>
<li>Birds will cause superficial injury to individuals on or approaching the Island.</li>
<li>Individuals die or go missing on the island.</li>
<li>There is some sort of entity on the island.</li>
</ul>
<p>Given these facts, a lost, confused seaman, likely suffering from hunger, thirst and sleep deprivation, has come to the conclusion that the birds are there explicitly to protect humans.</p>
<p>Given the same facts, I, as a reader, do not infer the same thing. My reading of this SCP gives me a different impression of it's purpose than the impressions of characters in it. Although this, in and of itself, is not necessarily a bad thing, for me it doesn't work in this instance.</p>

