<p>As I've said to you on IRC, the article feels like a skeleton despite its content.</p>
<p>I do think an armed/armoured team of Foundation agents exploring the island to figure out what's living there would add more value to the article as a whole. Something that would make the reader feel &#8220;Damn, I'm so glad it's stuck on an island. Totally warrants the artillery fire mentioned in the containment procedures.&#8221; without being too over the top. Just something to think about.</p>
<p><strong>Edit</strong>: I think the comparison I want to make is with <a href="/scp-184">The Architect</a>. By itself, you know everything you need to know about 184 but you just sit there wanting more. Then BAM, the exploration log hits you. It only gives you a glimpse of its capabilities and the beginning of the events that occured in its retrieval mission. No need to go into extra detail explaining what it is, just give us a loooong taste without actually being arbitrarily vague.</p>

							</div>

								
