<p>I've been thinking - the Foundation has been around for a long time. Anytime I see a story that has an early date to it, someone does another that pushes it back further.</p>
<p>Add to that that the fact that many articles are VERY vague as to date.</p>
<p>I'm wondering if you can have this as if it was written in the 1960s or earlier. Or parts written earlier where every decade they try to figure it out - and the closer they get, the worse the mystery becomes to solve.</p>
<p>Dunno. But rereading that, suddenly <strong>I'M</strong> starting to sound like <em>&quot;Previously, on LOST&#8230;.&quot;</em></p>

